When define method in a class like this:

```groovy
@CompileStatic
class App {
    @NamedVariant(coerce = true)
    void run(int number) {
        println(number)
    }
}
```

The generated method will also be compiled statically. So when I call the method:

```groovy
run(number: "123")
```

It will call `DefaultGroovyMethods.asType()` instead of `StringGroovyMethods.asType()`, so the string cannot convert to integer properly. So I must skip `@CompileStatic`.
In order to achieve this goal, I skip type checking explicitly.
